rdinary Circumstances on Review Periods\",\n            \"explanation\": \"Extraordinary circumstances can lead to an extension of the review period for applications beyond the standard 60 days. These situations may arise from complex factors that require a more in-depth examination of the application. This flexibility in the review process is important for ensuring that all relevant aspects are considered before a decision is made, thus enhancing the regulatory oversight of control transactions [Data: Entities (431); Relationships (541)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Importance of Filing Fees in the Application Process\",\n            \"explanation\": \"Filing fees are mandatory charges that must accompany applications for control transactions. These fees are essential for the processing of applications and are specified by regulatory rules. The requirement for filing fees ensures that the administrative and regulatory work can be conducted efficiently, facilitating the oversight and management of control transactions. This financial aspect underscores the seriousness of the application process and the commitment of applicants to comply with regulatory standards [Data: Entities (423); Relationships (533)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Evaluation of Financial Condition in Applications\",\n            \"explanation\": \"The financial condition of the acquiring person is a critical factor evaluated during the application process for control transactions. This assessment helps determine the potential impact on the bank's stability and overall financial health. By scrutinizing the financial background of applicants, the Commissioner can make informed decisions that protect the interests of stakeholders and maintain the integrity of the banking system [Data: Entities (427); Relationships (538)].\"\n        },\n        {\n            \"summary\": \"Assessment of Management Personnel in Control Transactions\",\n            \"